o%20test%20whether%20the%20government%20of%20the%20day%20enjoys%20the%20confidence%20of%20the%20majority%20of%20the%20house%2C%20as%20under%20a%20parliamentary%20democracy%2C%20a%20government%20can%20only%20be%20in%20power%20if%20it%20commands%20the%20majority%20in%20the%20directly%20elected%20house.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EArticle%2075(3)%20of%20the%20Indian%20constitution%20states%20that%20the%20Council%20of%20Ministers%20shall%20be%20responsible%20to%20the%20House%20of%20the%20People.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EUnder%20Rule%20198%20of%20the%20Rules%20of%20Procedure%20and%20Conduct%20of%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20a%20member%20has%20to%20move%20a%20written%20notice%20before%2010%20am%2C%20which%20will%20be%20read%20out%20by%20the%20speaker%20within%2010%20days%20of%20the%20written%20motion%20being%20submitted.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOnce%20the%20speaker%20reads%20out%20the%20motion%20in%20the%20House%2C%20a%20minimum%20of%2050%20members%20will%20have%20to%20rise%20in%20support%20of%20it%20for%20the%20speaker%20to%20give%20a%20date%20or%20dates%20for%20discussion%20of%20the%20motion.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELok%20Sabha%20speaker%20Om%20Birla%20has%20accepted%20the%20no-confidence%20motion%20moved%20by%20Gogoi%20and%20informed%20the%20house%20that%20a%20date%20will%20be%20set%20soon.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20present%20motion%20will%20be%20the%2028th%20no-confidence%20motion%20since%20Independence%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20the%20second%20faced%20by%20the%20Modi%20government.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EThe%20first%20no-confidence%20motion%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20first%20no-confidence%20motion%20was%20moved%20against%20the%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%20government%20in%201963%20by%20Acharya%20J.B.%20Kripalani%20over%20the%20prime%20minister%E2%80%99s%20China%20policy%2C%20immediately%20after%20the%201962%20war.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAccording%20to%20G.C.%20Malhotra%E2%80%99s%20book%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ECabinet%20Responsibility%20to%20Legislature%3A%20Motions%20of%20Confidence%20and%20No-Confidence%20in%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20State%20Legislatures%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20available%20in%20the%20Parliament%20digital%20library%2C%20the%20debate%20lasted%2021%20hours%20and%2033%20minutes%20spread%20over%20four%20days%20(August%2019-22%2C%201963).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20motion%20was%20supported%20by%2044%20members%20and%20when%20it%20was%20put%20to%20vote%2C%2062%20voted%20in%20favour%20while%20347%20MPs%20voted%20against%20it.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EIndira%20Gandhi%20faced%2015%20no-confidence%20motions%20in%20her%2016-year%20tenure%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndira%20Gandhi%20faced%20the%20most%20number%20of%20no-confidence%20motions%20in%20the%20history%20of%20independent%20India%2C%20with%2015%20motions%20during%20her%2016-year%20tenure%20(1966-77%20and%20then%20from%201980%20to%20her%20assassination%20in%20October%201984)%20as%20prime%20minister.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20were%2012%20motions%20of%20no-confidence%20in%20her%20first%20stint%2C%20including%20one%20moved%20by%20Atal%20Bihari%20Vajpayee%20in%201967%2C%20and%20three%20in%20her%20second.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F10%2F31182212%2FIndira-Gandhi.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F10%2F31182212%2FIndira-Gandhi.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F10%2F31182212%2FIndira-Gandhi-300x198.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F10%2F31182212%2FIndira-Gandhi-1024x676.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-306534%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22792%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EIndira%20Gandhi.%20Photo%3A%20Public.Resource.Org%2FFlickr%20CC%20BY%202.0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EFall%20of%20a%20government%20through%20a%20no-confidence%20motion%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20sixth%20Lok%20Sabha%20saw%20a%20non-Congress%20party%20in%20power%20for%20the%20first%20time%2C%20when%20a%20new%20government%20led%20by%20Morarji%20Desai%20won%20an%20overwhelming%20majority.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDesai%20faced%20two%20no-confidence%20motions.%20While%20he%20won%20the%20first%20one%2C%20the%20discussion%20on%20the%20second%20remained%20inconclusive%20but%20led%20to%20the%20fall%20of%20his%20government.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20motion%20was%20moved%20against%20Desai%20by%20Y.B.%20Chavan%20(Congress%20I)%20on%20July%2011%2C%201979%2C%20and%20claimed%20that%20there%20was%20a%20loss%20of%20confidence%20in%20the%20government%20in%20all%20walks%20of%20life.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAfter%20the%20discussion%20remained%20inconclusive%2C%20Desai%20on%20July%2015%20tendered%20his%20resignation%20to%20president%20Neelam%20Sanjiva%20Reddy.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EPrime%20ministers%20who%20faced%20no-confidence%20motions%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20look%20at%20the%20no-confidence%20motions%20faced%20by%20all%20prime%20ministers%20in%20independent%20India%20reveals%20that%20Lal%20Bahadur%20Shastri%20and%20P.V.%20Narasimha%20Rao%20faced%20three%20motions%20while%20Morarji%20Desai%20and%20Atal%20Bihari%20Vajpayee%20faced%20two%20motions%20each.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBoth%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%20and%20Rajiv%20Gandhi%20faced%20one%20motion%20each.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPrime%20ministers%20Charan%20Singh%2C%20V.P.%20Singh%2C%20Chandra%20Shekhar%2C%20H.D.%20Deve%20Gowda%20and%20I.K.%20Gujral%20did%20not%20face%20any%20such%20motion.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ERao%E2%80%99s%20third%20no-confidence%20motion%20mired%20in%20controversy%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERao%20faced%20three%20no-confidence%20motions%20and%20defeated%20all%20of%20them.%20But%20the%20third%20one%20faced%20by%20his%20government%20was%20mired%20in%20controversy.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20July%201993%2C%20Rao%20faced%20a%20no-confidence%20motion%20moved%20by%20the%20CPI(M)%20member%20Ajoy%20Mukhopadhyay.%20He%20won%20the%20vote%20with%20a%20narrow%20margin%20%E2%80%93%20251%20votes%20against%20his%20government%20to%20265%20votes%20in%20favour.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAccording%20to%20a%20PTI%20report%2C%20a%20year%20later%2C%20there%20was%20a%20scandal%20when%20it%20surfaced%20that%20Shibhu%20Soren%20of%20the%20Jharkhand%20Janmukti%20Morcha%20(JMM)%20and%20his%20four%20MPs%20had%20been%20paid%20bribes%20to%20vote%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20Rao%20government.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%201998%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20held%20in%20the%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%20P.V.%20Narasimha%20Rao%20versus%20CBI%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20case%20that%20parliamentarians%20had%20immunity%20under%20the%20constitution%20against%20criminal%20prosecution%20for%20any%20speech%20made%20and%20vote%20cast%20inside%20the%20house.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EUnder%20Article%20105(2)%20of%20the%20constitution%2C%20no%20MP%20shall%20be%20liable%20to%20any%20proceedings%20in%20any%20court%20in%20respect%20of%20anything%20said%20or%20any%20vote%20given%20by%20him%20in%20parliament%20or%20any%20committee%20thereof.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMLAs%20on%20the%20other%20hand%20are%20granted%20protection%20under%20Article%20194(2).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Union%20government%20last%20November%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Findia-news%2Fcentre-backs-verdict-protecting-lawmakers-from-prosecution-if-they-accept-cash-for-vote-in-house-101668538075264.html%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ebacked%20the%201998%20judgment.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EVajpayee%20years%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPrior%20to%20Modi%2C%20the%20last%20BJP%20government%20that%20faced%20a%20no-confidence%20motion%20was%20in%202003%2C%20when%20Vajpayee%20faced%20one%20moved%20by%20Sonia%20Gandhi.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EVajpayee%2C%20however%2C%20defeated%20the%20motion%20by%20a%20margin%20of%20125%20votes.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EVajpayee%20was%20also%20prime%20minister%20for%20two%20short%20stints%20in%201996%20and%20again%20from%201998-99.%20He%20had%20moved%20three%20motions%20of%20confidence%2C%20trying%20to%20prove%20his%20majority%20in%20the%20house.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20lost%20the%20third%20one%20in%20April%201999%20by%20just%20one%20vote%20%E2%80%93%20which%20resulted%20in%20the%20premature%20dissolution%20of%20the%2012th%20Lok%20Sabha%20because%20the%20opposition%20was%20also%20not%20able%20to%20muster%20the%20numbers%20to%20form%20a%20government.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F08%2F27170301%2FAtal_Bihari_Vajpayee_PTI.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F08%2F27170301%2FAtal_Bihari_Vajpayee_PTI.jpg%20900w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F08%2F27170301%2FAtal_Bihari_Vajpayee_PTI-300x150.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F08%2F27170301%2FAtal_Bihari_Vajpayee_PTI-800x400.jpg%20800w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-283557%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22450%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EAtal%20Bihari%20Vajpayee.%20Photo%3A%20PTI%2FFiles%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EModi%E2%80%99s%20no-confidence%20motion%20in%202018%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20no-confidence%20motion%20moved%20by%20the%20Congress%20will%20be%20the%20second%20one%20faced%20by%20Modi%20in%20his%20nine-year%20tenure.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%202018%2C%20Modi%20defeated%20his%20first%20no-confidence%20motion.%20Speaker%20Sumitra%20Mahajan%20had%20named%20all%20opposition%20members%20who%20had%20moved%20similar%20no-confidence%20motions%20and%20said%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fon-first-day-of-monsoon-session-no-confidence-motion-moved-against-modi-govthttps%3A%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fon-first-day-of-monsoon-session-no-confidence-motion-moved-against-modi-govt%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ETelugu%20Desam%20Party%E2%80%99s%20Kesineni%20Srinivas%20would%20move%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Cspan%3Ehis%20motion%20as%20his%20name%20had%20come%20up%20in%20the%20lottery.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAfter%20a%20raging%2012-hour%20debate%2C%20the%20Modi%20government%20defeated%20the%20no-confidence%20motion%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20by%20199%20votes.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20total%20of%20126%20members%20supported%20the%20motion%2C%20while%20325%20MPs%20rejected%20it.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20debate%20is%20remembered%20for%20Congress%20leader%20Rahul%20Gandhi%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Frahul-gandhi-attack-narendra-modi-congress-monsoon-session%5C%22%3Eembracing%20the%20prime%20minister%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20delivering%20a%20speech%20in%20which%20he%20questioned%20the%20government%20and%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20silence%20on%20the%20rising%20crimes%20against%20minori