fish.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20research%20from%20a%20variety%20of%20areas%20points%20to%20a%20more%20positive%20view%20of%20humanity.%20Along%20with%20the%20study%20of%20heroism%2C%20the%20field%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpositivepsychology.com%2Fwhat-is-positive-psychology-definition%2F%5C%22%3Epositive%20psychology%3C%2Fa%3E%20(established%20during%20the%20early%202000s)%20studies%20human%20wellbeing%20and%20researches%20traits%20such%20as%20wisdom%2C%20courage%2C%20gratitude%20and%20resilience.%20Positive%20psychologists%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpositivepsychology.com%2Fpositive-psychology-theory%2F%5C%22%3EMartin%20Seligman%3C%2Fa%3E%20argue%20conventional%20psychology%20had%20for%20too%20long%20been%20essentially%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20study%20of%20unhappiness%E2%80%9D%20and%20that%20a%20new%20field%20was%20needed%20to%20study%20what%20%E2%80%9Cis%20good%20or%20virtuous%20in%20human%20nature%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20consensus%20from%20anthropologists%20is%20that%2C%20for%20the%20vast%20majority%20of%20the%20time%20that%20we%E2%80%99ve%20inhabited%20this%20planet%2C%20human%20societies%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fwhy-our-ancestors-were-more-gender-equal-than-us-41902%5C%22%3Ehave%20been%20egalitarian%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fblogs.scientificamerican.com%2Fcross-check%2Fnew-study-of-prehistoric-skeletons-undermines-claim-that-war-has-deep-evolutionary-roots%2F%5C%22%3Epeaceful%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20challenges%20the%20neo-Darwinist%20idea%20that%20human%20life%20has%20always%20been%20a%20competitive%20struggle%20for%20survival%2C%20conditioning%20us%20to%20be%20selfish%20and%20individualistic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20forerunner%20of%20positive%20psychology%2C%20Abraham%20Maslow%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.positivedisintegration.com%2Fmasid.htm%5C%22%3Esaid%20in%201968%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20human%20nature%20has%20been%20%E2%80%9Csold%20short%E2%80%